results.name: Number of normal generalized Young tableaux, of shape the integer partition with Heinz number n, with all rows and columns strictly increasing.
comment: A generalized Young tableau of shape y is an array obtained by replacing the dots in the Ferrers diagram of y with positive integers. A tableau is normal if its entries span an initial interval of positive integers. The Heinz number of an integer partition (y_1,...,y_k) is prime(y_1)*...*prime(y_k).
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Feb 26 2018
